description:
&lt;p&gt;The Microbiology department is looking to appoint enthusiastic, well-motivated individuals to join our busy and friendly department within the BMS team at band 5/6 levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based at The James Cook University Hospital, the laboratory provides a wide range of investigations to support the clinical activity within a busy Trust and surrounding GP population. The Microbiology Laboratory is modern, well equipped and fully computerised offering a wide range of manual, automated and semi-automated tests for Bacteriology, Virology and Molecular diagnostics. The laboratory processes approximately 400,000 specimens per year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will acquire a good range of experience by rotation through all sections of the laboratory&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Microbiology department operates a 24/7 service, when suitably trained participation in out of hours working will be required, including night shifts, weekends and Bank Holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For both these roles the candidates will need to HCPC registered and for band 6 roles the applicants will need to hold a specialist portfolio in Microbiology/Virology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
